  "prompt": "Which is a good refrence book for Servlets and JSP?",
  "response": "A highly recommended reference book for Servlets and JSP is \"Head First Servlets and JSP\" by Bryan Basham, Kathy Sierra, and Bert Bates. It's known for presenting complex concepts in an engaging and accessible way, making it easier to understand and apply server-side Java technologies.\n\nAnother good reference is \"Core Servlets and JavaServer Pages\" by Marty Hall and Larry Brown. This book provides detailed explanations and practical examples that can help in mastering Servlets and JSP.\n\nBoth of these books are well-regarded in the Java community and can be very helpful for both beginners and experienced developers looking to deepen their understanding of Java web technologies.",
